title: Marc Chagall America Windows Magnet Set
description:
Magnet developed from Marc Chagall’s America Windows, 1977, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Our set of 3 magnets are adapted from Marc Chagall’s (French, born Vitebsk, Russia; present-day Belarus, 1887-1985) famed America Windows, a symphony of color in stained glass created to celebrate the U.S. bicentennial.

  • Set of 3 magnets
  • Dimensions: 3 x 2 in. each.
